---
description: Always send function responses back to Gemini after handling tool calls
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx}"
alwaysApply: false
---

When handling Gemini function calls, you MUST send a function response back via the WebSocket.

Tool calls arrive as TOP-LEVEL `toolCall` messages (not inside serverContent.modelTurn.parts).

Two response strategies based on tool type:

**UI-only tools** (show_overlay, clear_overlays, advance_step) — use SILENT scheduling to prevent double-speech:
```json
{
  "toolResponse": {
    "functionResponses": [{
      "id": "<call.id>",
      "name": "<call.name>",
      "response": { "success": true },
      "scheduling": "SILENT"
    }]
  }
}
```

**State-feedback tools** (show_diagnosis, generate_report, complete_procedure) — normal response:
```json
{
  "toolResponse": {
    "functionResponses": [{
      "id": "<call.id>",
      "name": "<call.name>",
      "response": { "success": true }
    }]
  }
}
```

Also handle `toolCallCancellation` messages — these arrive when the user interrupts during a tool call. Remove the cancelled call IDs from pending state.

DEDUPLICATION: Track processed call IDs. Skip duplicate IDs and duplicate tool names within the same batch.

Forgetting to send the function response breaks Gemini's conversation loop. This applies to EVERY function call.
